Executive Function Coaching for Students

Struggling with time management, organization, or motivation? Our executive function coaching for students helps kids and teens develop essential skills to thrive in school, at home, and in life.

Sign Up for a Free Discovery Call Now!

Executive function coaching for students provides structured support in areas like time management, task initiation, organization, and follow-through. With personalized strategies, students learn to stay on top of schoolwork, build academic confidence, and achieve long-term success.

If your child struggles with:
Procrastination or incomplete homework,
Disorganization and forgetfulness, or
Staying focused and managing time effectively,
they may need support with executive functioning.

Understanding Cognitive Skills

What is Executive Function Coaching for Kids, Teens, and Young Adults?

Many students struggle with executive functioning challenges, making it difficult to stay organized, plan ahead, and complete tasks independently. Whether your child has general difficulties with self-management, ADHD, or autism, our executive functioning specialists provide structured support to help them overcome executive dysfunction and build lifelong success strategies.

Planning and Prioritizing

Breaking big tasks into smaller, manageable steps.

Organization

Keeping track of assignments, materials, and schedules.

Focus and Attention

Staying engaged and avoiding distractions.

Task Initiation

Starting work without procrastinating.

Emotional Regulation

Managing frustration and stress during challenging tasks

When these skills arent fully developed, students may experience executive dysfunction, which makes even simple tasks feel impossible to manage.

Why Choose New Frontiers

We dont believe in one-size-fits-all solutions.

Our coaches use structured models like RASP (Review, Assess, Strategize, Plan) and RISE (Recognize Problems, Identify Strategies, Strategy Implementation, and Evaluate Effectiveness) to design a plan that works for your child. We tailor our coaching to meet their specific needs, helping them overcome challenges and unlock their potential.

Executive Functioning Skills for Teens and Kids

How We Help: Executive Function Coaching Tailored to Your Students Needs

With the right support, students can go from feeling overwhelmed to feeling empowered. Our coaching helps students:

Improve time management and organization

Learn how to use planners, calendars, and reminders to track assignments and meet deadlines.

Enhance task initiation and follow-through

Overcome procrastination and develop the ability to start and complete tasks on time.

Strengthen working memory and cognitive flexibility

Improve problem-solving, adaptability, and processing skills.

Develop self-advocacy and independent learning strategies

Learn how to communicate needs effectively and take ownership of learning.

Build emotional regulation and stress management skills

Reduce frustration, anxiety, and meltdowns related to schoolwork.

Improve study habits and test preparation

Develop personalized techniques for note-taking, memorization, and exam readiness.

For teens, especially, this is a critical time to develop habits and skills that will carry them into adulthood.

The Journey to Coaching

Coaching is a collaborative process designed to provide the right support at the right time. Our structured approach ensures that every student receives a tailored coaching experience that fosters growth, accountability, and long-term success.

01

Explore & Define

Discovery Call
We start with a conversation with parents or stakeholders to understand key challenges and goals.

Consultation
We meet with the student to gain insight into their strengths, struggles, and what they hope to achieve.

02

Plan & Pair

Coaching Plan 
We create a personalized roadmap using evidence-based strategies aligned with the students needs.

Coach Match
We carefully select a coach whose expertise and approach fit the students personality and goals.

03

Begin Your Journey

Initial Session
The student and coach establish a working relationship and begin building executive function skills.

Using RISE & RASP
Our structured models provide a clear framework for problem-solving, strategy development, and self-reflection.

04

Sustain Growth

Accountability & Follow-Through Coaching provides ongoing support to ensure strategies are implemented effectively.

Building Lasting Habits
As students gain confidence, they develop independence and long-term success beyond coaching.

Frequently Asked Questions

You ask, we
answer

Common questions answered to support your childs journey.

What is executive function coaching?

Its a personalized approach to helping students develop essential skills like organization, focus, and time management.

How does coaching help with executive dysfunction?

Through one-on-one support, students learn practical strategies to manage their workload, stay organized, and overcome procrastination.

Whats the difference between tutoring and executive function coaching?

Tutoring focuses on specific subjects, while coaching addresses the underlying skills that impact academic success across all areas.

Can coaching help students with ADHD or autism?

Yes! We specialize in supporting students with ADHD and autism, helping them build routines, manage emotions, and improve focus.

Is executive function coaching the same as executive function or executive dysfunction therapy?

No, executive function coaching is not the same as therapy. In fact, there isnt a formalized approach or discipline called executive function therapy. While therapy often focuses on addressing emotional or psychological issues, coaching is a practical, hands-on approach to building skills like time management, organization, and focus. <br>
